        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injuries.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the negative cable from the battery terminal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the thermostat from the sleeper control panel,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116011">Figure 1, Item 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the harness connector from the thermostat and push the connector and harness
                    back into the thermostat hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the other end of the harness as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116011">Figure 1, Item 2</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bunk cabinets and paneling sufficiently to route new harness, Part Number
                    3556220C91, as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116012">Figure 2, Item 5</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use friction tape, Part Number 2643119R1, to secure the temperature transmitter to the
                    paneling as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116012">Figure 2, Item 2</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the new harness connector as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116012">Figure 2, Item 4</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the new harness with tie straps as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116012">Figure 2, Item 3</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the cabinets and paneling.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the thermostat to the rear outside of the cabinet as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116012">Figure 2, Item 1</hotlnk>. The template for hole sizes and locations are
                    shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0116013">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the negative battery cable to the battery.</para>
            </step1>
